timelineItems.desc: The San Jose Earthquakes will put their record shutout streak on the line and their hold on a playoff position in the Western Conference when they face a Philadelphia Union trying to crawl back into the reckoning in the Eastern Conference as the clubs meet at Avaya Stadium on Saturday evening.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: San Jose Earthquakes vs Philadelphia Union | September 5, 2015

timelineItems.name: Jonathan Tannenwald
timelineItems.text: Jim Curtin's substitutions pay off. Now excuse me while I leave my computer to go down to the locker room. #SJvPHI

timelineItems.name: Jimbo Lamb
timelineItems.text: I just don't understand this team. Three points in the road against one of the hottest in-form teams in the league. #DOOP

timelineItems.name: Phil Giangiulio
timelineItems.text: Well that was worth staying up for 2-1 #Union Win! #Doop

timelineItems.name: Bill Sandone
timelineItems.text: WINNER!!!!!!! #DOOP

timelineItems.name: Jonathan Molik
timelineItems.text: UNION WIN!! Absolutely amazing road win!! #DOOP #SJvPHI

timelineItems.name: Derrick
timelineItems.text: Great game for all players minus that random Fabi handball. Barnetta looked good through the middle. Big road win!!! #DOOP

timelineItems.name: Philadelphia Union
timelineItems.text: FINAL SJ 1- 2 PHI: The Union win for the first time in San Jose! Conor Casey with both goals #SJvPHI #DOOP

timelineItems.name: Joe Tansey
timelineItems.text: And with two flicks of Conor Casey's head, the Union are in 7th place and 1 point behind Montreal for 6th. #DOOP #SJvPHI
